      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please confirm: an independent frame (requiredFrame \u003d\u003d kNoFrame) means we start from a zero-initialized buffer, not an uninitialized buffer, right?\n\nI think that my earlier confusion re requiredFrames was basically that I thought independent meant that we could start from an uninitialized buffer. Theoretically, we could identify \"super-independent\" frames, a subset of independent frames, that could start from an uninitialized pixel buffer (if fully received), and therefore skip some redundant zero-initialization, but Skia doesn\u0027t already have this concept, right?",
      "revId": "1d001032647bb2f658edc8a71fd28aaacd5e9fe6",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ce42fc1b_90ad6cf4",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 744,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-04T20:33:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Please confirm: an independent frame (requiredFrame \u003d\u003d kNoFrame) means we start from a zero-initialized buffer, not an uninitialized buffer, right?\n\nNo. It is intended that SkCodec will initialize all pixels, unless some are expected to have been initialized by the prior frame (e.g. the new frame is not independent). That doesn\u0027t mean we don\u0027t have a bug.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e I think that my earlier confusion re requiredFrames was basically that I thought independent meant that we could start from an uninitialized buffer.\n\nThat is the intent.\n\n\u003e Theoretically, we could identify \"super-independent\" frames, a subset of independent frames, that could start from an uninitialized pixel buffer (if fully received), and therefore skip some redundant zero-initialization, but Skia doesn\u0027t already have this concept, right?\n\nI do not understand what a \"super-independent\" frame is, but I think it depends on the misunderstanding above.",
      "parentUuid": "62f97247_129809d2",
      "revId": "1d001032647bb2f658edc8a71fd28aaacd5e9fe6",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
